#item-change-processes.doc-content 
    h1 insertChangeProcesses( link, params);
    .definition Insert related change processes with advanced filtering and create capabilities 
        br
        |This function gets included in all pages automatically and is defined in 
        span.path /public/javascripts/contents/item.js
        |. 
        img(src='images/docs/item-change-processes-1.png' style='display:block;margin-top:20px;height:202px;')
    h2 DOM Elements 
    p Insert the following base element to your pug file to add the grid container in your page. You can choose another id than shown here, but will then have to provide your element's id as parameter.
    p.code #processes 
    p Add the following optional classes to this DOM element to adjust the contents display:
    p 
        table.row-hovering 
            tr 
                th Class Name 
                th Description
            tr 
                td surface-level-[1..5]
                td Add the UI classes surface-level-1 through surface-level-5 to adjust the background color of the grid element 
    h2 Parameters
    p Various parameters can be provided when using insertGrid. The link parameter is required and must be provided as string to identify the record for which the related processes should be shown. 
    p.code insertChangeProcesses('/api/v3/workspaces/57/items/4810', { headerLabel : 'Problem Reports', actions : ['create'], workspacesIn : ['Problem Reports'] });
    p The following table lists all parameters available inlcuding their default values:
    p   
        table.parameters.row-hovering 
            tr 
                th.nowrap Parameter 
                th Description
                th Type 
                th Required 
                th Default 
            tr 
                td link 
                td The API-link of the item to be displayed
                td String
                td Yes
                td -
            tr 
                td id 
                td ID of the DOM element where the processes list &amp; create form will be inserted
                td String
                td No
                td processes 
            tr 
                td header 
                td Can be used to suppress addition of the panel header element. This must be set to true if toolbar actions (i.e. reload) should be shown.
                td Boolean
                td No
                td true
            tr 
                td headerLabel
                td Sets the header label (if header is enabled)
                td String
                td No
                td Processes
            tr 
                td headerToggle 
                td Enables collapsing and expanding the panel
                td Boolean
                td No 
                td false
            tr 
                td compactDisplay 
                td Enables a compact display using additional css settings
                td Boolean
                td No 
                td false
            tr 
                td openInPLM 
                td Adds a button to open selected element in PLM. Users can always open a given record in PLM by double-clicking the record. 
                td Boolean
                td No 
                td true
            tr 
                td filterByWorkspace 
                td Enable filtering by workspace drop down. The drop down will only be shown if there are multiple different values to choose from.
                td Boolean
                td No 
                td true
            tr 
                td search 
                td Adds quick filtering using search input on top of list
                td Boolean
                td No
                td true
            tr 
                td placeholder 
                td Set placeholder text for quick filtering input
                td String
                td No
                td Type to search
            tr 
                td reload 
                td Enables / disables the reload button 
                td Boolean
                td No
                td true    
            tr 
                td actions 
                td Defines the available actions to modify the list (ie ['create']). Currenlty, only 'create' is supported.
                td Array
                td No
                td []
            tr 
                td layout 
                td Set layout (select from 'table', 'tiles' or 'list')
                td String
                td No
                td list
            tr 
                td number 
                td When set to true, a number will be displayed as first column or instead of the tile icon in case of tiles / list layout
                td Boolean
                td No
                td true
            tr 
                td tileIcon 
                td Icon to be displayed as tile image 
                td String
                td No
                td icon-status
            tr 
                td tileSize 
                td Tile size (gets applied only for layouts 'tiles' and 'list', select from 'xxxs', 'xxs', 'xs', 's', 'm', 'l', 'xl', 'xxl')
                td String
                td No
                td xs
            tr 
                td tableHeaders 
                td When set to false, the table headers will not be shown
                td Boolean
                td No
                td true
            tr 
                td columnsIn 
                td Restricts the columns to be displayed. If this list is not empty, only the columns in this list will be shown. Select from the standard tab columns ('Workflow Item', 'Workspace', ...).
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td columnsEx 
                td Restricts the columns to be displayed. If this list is not empty, the columns in this list will not be shown. Select from the standard tab columns ('Workflow Item', 'Workspace', ...).
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td workspacesIn 
                td List of workspace to be included, identified by workspace names (example: ['Change Orders'])
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td workspacesEx 
                td List of workspace to be excluded, identified by workspace names (example: ['Problem Reports', 'Change Tasks'])
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td workspacesIn 
                td List of workspace to be included, identified by workspace IDs. Workspaces not included in this list will not be shown (example: ['82']).
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td workspacesEx 
                td List of workspace to be excluded, identified by workspace ID. Workspacess in this list will not be shown (example: ['83','84']).
                td Array
                td No 
                td []               
            tr 
                td createHeaderLabel 
                td If creation of new records is enabled (using parameter createWSID), this option sets the create dialog header.
                td Array
                td No 
                td 'Create Process'
            tr 
                td createSectionsIn 
                td If creation of new records is enabled (using parameter action), this list can be used to select the sections to be shown in the create dialog. Only sections of this list will be shown (example: ['Header','Details']).
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td createSectionsEx 
                td If creation of new records is enabled (using parameter action), this list can be used to hide sections in the create dialog. Sections of this list will not be shown (example: ['Review']).
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td createFieldsIn 
                td If creation of new records is enabled (using parameter action), this list can be used to select the fields to be shown in the create dialog. Only fields of this list will be shown (example: ['Title','Description']).
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td createFieldsEx 
                td If creation of new records is enabled (using parameter action), this list can be used to hide fields in the create dialog. Fields of this list will not be shown (example: ['Closing Comment']).
                td Array
                td No 
                td []
            tr 
                td onItemClick 
                td Provide a function to be executed when users click an item (table row or tile). Example : 
                    br
                    |onItemClick : function(elemClicked) { elemClicked.hide(); }
                td function
                td No 
                td null                
            tr 
                td createContext 
                td Provide context item information if default value should be set in linking pick list field
                    br
                    |Example: { title : 'P-00001 - Assembly', link : '/api/v3/workspaces/57/items/382', fieldId : 'AFFECTED_ITEM' })
                td JSON
                td No 
                td null
