    h2 Events 
    p You can override the following functions in your code to adjust the default behavior.
    p 
        table.row-hovering
            tr 
                th Function 
                th Event 
                th Parameters 
                th Default Behavior
            tr 
                td insertChangeProcessesDone(id, data) 
                td Gets executed once process information has been retrieved from PLM and after data has been inserted to the page.
                td 
                    ul 
                        li id = id of the parent div element (i.e. processes)
                        li data = data of /change-processes REST API call of PLM
                td - none -
            tr 
                td insertChangeProcessesData(id) 
                td This function gets triggered after insertChangeProcessesDone(id) and when users click the refresh button. It retrieves data from PLM and updates the data being displayed.
                td id of the parent div element (i.e. processes)
                td Inserts processes data and sets filter controls. Once completed, it triggers insertChangeProcessesDataDone(id, data).
            tr 
                td insertChangeProcessesDataDone(id, data) 
                td This gets triggered by insertChangeProcessesData(id) once the data has been retrieved from PLM and when the given data has been inserted to the HTML page
                td
                    ul 
                        li id = id of the parent div
                        li data = response data of given API call
                td - none -